**Verdict:** yes, unwired `ILM_*`, especially `ILM_visuals.tre`, is consistent with both symptoms. 
The cfg manifest is incomplete for JTL space.

Evidence:

- Ship load path is direct:
  `ClientShipObjectTemplate::createObject()` creates `ShipObject` at `src/engine/client/library/clien
tGame/src/shared/objectTemplate/ClientShipObjectTemplate.cpp:121-123`.
  `ShipObject` calls `TangibleObject(newTemplate)` at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/object/ShipObject.cpp:284-285`.
  `TangibleObject` reads `objectTemplate.getAppearanceFilename()` and calls 
`AppearanceTemplateList::createAppearance()` at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/object/TangibleObject.cpp:599-604`.
  `AppearanceTemplateList::fetch()` checks `TreeFile::exists(fileName)` and, if absent, logs “using 
default” and substitutes `appearance/defaultappearance.apt` at 
`src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/appearance/AppearanceTemplateList.cpp:230-234`; 
default name is defined at `:55`.
  So a ship appearance missing from the search path becomes the default placeholder, exactly 
matching the observed missing-model ship.

- `TreeFile` only loads what cfg names:
  `TreeFile::install()` walks `searchPath`, `searchTree`, and `searchTOC` keys from `[SharedFile]` 
at `src/engine/shared/library/sharedFile/src/shared/TreeFile.cpp:117-147`.
  `TreeFile::exists()` returns lookup success from loaded nodes at `:471-482`.
  `TreeFile::open(..., allowFail=true)` returns `NULL` instead of fatal if not found at `:742-750`.

- Space environment load is data-driven and mostly degrades, not fatal:
  Terrain file must exist or fatal: `GroundScene::load()` checks `TreeFile::exists(terrainFileName)` 
at `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/scene/GroundScene.cpp:1317`, then loads it as an 
appearance at `:1324-1325`.
  Space terrain `.trn` carries clear color, ambient, parallel lights, distant appearances/planets, 
and celestials/shaders in `SpaceTerrainAppearanceTemplate.cpp:367-389` and `:500-530`.
  Runtime scene id becomes `space_*`, then `NebulaManagerClient::loadScene(ms_sceneId)` runs at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1450-1455`.
