Evidence:

- Ship load path is direct:
  `ClientShipObjectTemplate::createObject()` creates `ShipObject` at `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/objectTemplate/ClientShipObjectTemplate.cpp:121-123`.
  `ShipObject` calls `TangibleObject(newTemplate)` at `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/object/ShipObject.cpp:284-285`.
  `TangibleObject` reads `objectTemplate.getAppearanceFilename()` and calls `AppearanceTemplateList::createAppearance()` at `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/object/TangibleObject.cpp:599-604`.
  `AppearanceTemplateList::fetch()` checks `TreeFile::exists(fileName)` and, if absent, logs “using default” and substitutes `appearance/defaultappearance.apt` at `src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/appearance/AppearanceTemplateList.cpp:230-234`; default name is defined at `:55`.
  So a ship appearance missing from the search path becomes the default placeholder, exactly matching the observed missing-model ship.

- `TreeFile` only loads what cfg names:
  `TreeFile::install()` walks `searchPath`, `searchTree`, and `searchTOC` keys from `[SharedFile]` at `src/engine/shared/library/sharedFile/src/shared/TreeFile.cpp:117-147`.
